
[1]proverbial

   PROVERB'IAL,a. Mentioned in a proverb; as a proverbial cure or remedy.

   In case of excesses, I take the German proverbial cure, by a hair of
   the same beast, to be the worst in the world.

   1. Comprised in a proverb; used or current as a proverb; as a
   proverbial saying or speech.

   2. Pertaining to proverbs; resembling a proverb; suitable to a proverb;
   as a proverbial obscurity.
